{"word":"παρακρούω","slug":"παρακρούω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παρακρούω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>σω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to strike aside: to disappoint, mislead</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be led astray, go wrong</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—so also in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> also, <i>to strike away from oneself, parry</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}